Lowell Senior Center on 02/06/2021

276 Broadway Street, Lowell MA, 01854

Vaccinations offered: Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine

Age groups served: Other

Services offered: Vaccination

Additional Information: THIS CLINIC IS RESTRICTED TO LOWELL. Individuals who register for this clinic must meet BOTH criteria: 1.) must live or work in LOWELL AND 2.) must be eligible to receive vaccine in Phase 1 or be 75 years of age or older (eligible in Phase 2 Step 1). By signing up for an appointment, you are verifying that you meet this criteria and are available for the selected appointment time on MONDAY, 2/1. You must complete a Self-Attestation form in order to receive the vaccine. Instructions to complete the form prior to your appointment can be found here: https://www.mass.gov/forms/covid-19-massachusetts-vaccination-attestation-form OR you may complete the form upon arrival for your appointment. PLEASE DO NOT ENTER THE BUILDING BEFORE THE TIME OF YOUR APPOINTMENT. We will not be able to admit patients early. Please review your eligibility and bring a form of identification listed here: https://www.mass.gov/info-details/covid-19-vaccine-locations-for-individuals-currently-eligible-to-be-vaccinated.

Clinic Hours : 10:00 am - 01:45 pm

Available Appointments : 0

Special Instructions: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

Reggie Lewis State Track Athletic Ctr on 02/08/2021

1350 Tremont Street , Roxbury MA, 02120

Vaccinations offered: Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine

Age groups served: Adults, Seniors

Services offered: Vaccination

Additional Information: ***This clinic is intended for all eligible priority groups per the Commonwealth of Massachusetts’ vaccine distribution timeline that live or work in the City of Boston, regardless of immigration status. ID is not required. Pre-registration for this vaccination clinic is required. You must register using a unique email address for each person signing up to receive the vaccine. You cannot use the same email address for multiple people. ***Please arrive no more than 10 minutes before your appointment and remember to wear a mask and practice social distancing at all times. If you arrive early you will be asked to wait. Wear clothing that allows ease of access to the upper arm. All recipients will be required to stay for at least 15 minutes after the vaccine is administered for monitoring. ***Please review the fact sheet for the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine, available in multiple languages: https://www.fda.gov/emergency-preparedness-and-response/coronavirus-disease-2019-covid-19/pfizer-biontech-covid-19-vaccine. ***Please also complete the Massachusetts Attestation Form either online (https://www.mass.gov/forms/covid-19-massachusetts-vaccination-attestation-form) or print out a copy (https://www.mass.gov/lists/covid-19-vaccine-attestation-form-translations). Bring the completed form with you to your appointment or have a copy available on your phone. Forms will be available on-site if needed. This is a short form that you fill out to confirm that you are on the current list of eligible priority groups to receive the COVID-19 vaccination. *** If you were placed on the waitlist, someone will call if a spot becomes available. Do not show up to the clinic unless you are notified of an available spot.

Clinic Hours : 12:00 pm - 06:00 pm

Available Appointments : 0

Special Instructions: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
